==English==
===Etymology===
OE. [[altogedere]]; al all + togedere together.  See [[Together]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ɔl.tuˈgɛθ.ɚ/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛðə(r)|-ɛðə(r)]]

===Adverb===
# Without exception; wholly; completely.
#* ''Your advice will be altogether invaluable to me.'' &mdash;Doyle
# On the whole; with everything considered: 
#* ''Altogether, I'm sorry it happened.''
